<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-537-036  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 537 036.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  May 28 1990 v36 n1811 p38(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Samsung distributors hedge bets by courting competitive lines.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ferguson, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Samsung distributors are turning to competitors' products to avoidgetting stuck with DRAM inventories as a result of Samsung'ssupplier commodity program.andP;  Bell Microproducts signed anall-sites franchise agreement with Fujitsu Microelectronics Inc;Jaco Electronics, Samsung's largest distributor, aligned itselfwith Oki Semiconductor in a franchise deal.andP;  According to a BellMicro source, margin, profitability and customer service issuesforced the company to disengage with its offshore vendor.andO;According to a Jaco source, the company's decision was simply amove to align itself with a good product line independent ofSamsung.andP;  The same source feels that unless Samsung reinstatesconventional inventory and pricing protection, it will not be ableto continue its US distribution.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Samsung Group (distribution)Bell Microproducts Inc. (distribution)Fujitsu Microelectronics Inc. (contracts)Oki Semiconductor (contracts).andO;Ticker:    JACO.andO;Topic:     Semiconductor industryDistribution AgreementsMarketing StrategyDistributorsVendor Relations.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>